title: Mother Tuckers Yellow Duck - Home Grown Stuff (Canadian Rock 196
description:
Very hard to find official and very limited reissue on EMI Canada of the killer first album by this legendary Candian \&#039;60\&#039;s psych band with Guess Who connections. A mixture of West Coast melodic acid rock/pop (similar to Moby Grape) and rural hippy psych (Quicksilver/Dead) this 1969 album features amazing sustained guitar work on tracks like \"Times Are Changing\" and the scorching \"One Ring Jane\". Things get spacey and mellow during the dreamy psych of \"Elevated Platform\" and, overall, this album is a gem from start to finish. Awesome sound quality and the original artwork !
